issue.title: Audio Transmission Flawed?
issue.body:
Kind of weird to send the Audio via repeated POST requests. We should probably use a protocol that was intended for this, such as websocket instead? Or maybe bypass the endpoint and go directly to the backend? Otherwise we have two backends, one in next and one in python..

_Originally posted by @Ce-eM in https://github.com/oberpierre/uzh-masterproject/pull/1#discussion_r2280908751_

comment.body:
- Each POST request (every 100ms?) has significant HTTP header overhead
- Requires base64/JSON encoding/decoding

Defies the whole purpose of using a highly efficient binary encoded transmission protocol like protobuf.

performed_via_github_app.description:
SonarQube Cloud (formerly SonarCloud) is a SaaS code analysis tool designed to detect coding issues in 30+ languages, frameworks, and IaC platforms. Your code is checked against an extensive set of rules that cover many attributes of code, such as maintainability, reliability, and security issues, on each merge/pull request.

For those requiring US-based hosting, [SonarQube Cloud US](https://sonarqube.us/) offers the perfect alternative. If you need data residency outside the US or within the EU, [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/) with this GitHub app is the ideal solution.

SonarQube Cloud integrates seamlessly into your GitHub workflow and provides clear guidance for resolving any code quality and security issues detected. The majority of popular languages can be analyzed automatically; no configuration is required!

With [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/github), you get:

-   Fast, precise static analysis and feedback on your code
    
-   Support for popular languages, frameworks, and IaC tools
    
-   Free analysis for open-source projects and private projects up to max 50k LoC
    
-   Automatic analysis of pull requests and branches with results reported inline
    
-   IDE Support with [SonarQube for IDE](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarlint/) integration
    
-   Quality Gate (added as a GitHub check) acting at two different levels - first, preventing you from merging pull requests that contain issues - and later, helping you to release only clean, safe code
    
-   Sign up for SonarQube free tier and begin scanning your private and public repositories
    

A [GitHub Action](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/sonarcloud-scan) is available in the marketplace to make it easy for you (for projects where automatic analysis isn't available). SonarQube Cloud also integrates smoothly with Jenkins, CircleCI, TravisCI, CirrusCI, and many other tools.

A free tier is available that allows you to explore the benefits of SonarQube Cloud using your public and private repositories. We also provide a no-commitment, [14-day trial](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/) of SonarQube Cloud Team for unlimited team members, up to 1.9M LoC, AI CodeFix recommendations, and more. No need to speak with a sales rep or request a license key - get automatic code analysis results on your private projects in minutes! Want to see more examples of SonarCloud in action? You can [explore current Open Source projects in SonarCloud](https://sonarcloud.io/explore/projects?sort=-analysis_date) that are using the [Clean as You Code](https://www.sonarsource.com/solutions/our-unique-approach/) methodology.

What are you waiting for? SonarQube Cloud helps you consistently deliver cleaner, secure software that future developers will appreciate and your users will love. Start writing Clean Code. [Now](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/)!

### The AI Code Review Platform

## Get Started
Simply sign into Github and click the "Configure" button

## Overview
Qodo Merge automates review workflows, indentifies issues, and suggests quality improvements with instant analysis, smart feedback, and an interactive AI chat.

Supports 15+ powerful workflows — including /describe, /compliance, /improve, /implement, /custom_prompt, /generate_labels, /checks, and more.

Qodo adapts to your team’s standards, optimizes feedback relevance, and gets smarter over time.

Cut review time. Improve quality. On your terms.

**Qodo Merge Pro Capabilities:**

[Qodo Merge](https://qodo-merge-docs.qodo.ai/overview/pr_agent_pro/) is a hosted version of the [PR-Agent Open Source](https://github.com/qodo-ai/pr-agent) project, provided by Qodo. It offers a free tier with a monthly limit of PR reviews per organization, with subscription options available for higher usage.

- **15+ Automated Workflow Tools Including:**
  - `/describe`: Automatically generates pull request descriptions, titles, changes walkthroughs, and more.
  - `/compliance`:  Generates comprehensive compliance checks on PR code changes, task ticket requirements, and custom organizational compliance checklists.
  - `/review`: Generates a high-level review guide with key issues.
  - `/improve`: Iterate on PRs with dynamic, context-aware code suggestions.

- **Context-Aware Code Reviews and Suggestions:**
   Qodo Merge fetches context from your PR data, tickets, and collects your best practices to generate relevant code suggestions and feedback.

- **Automatic Learning:**
  Qodo Merge looks for repeated patterns in the suggestions that you accept and applies learnings to future code suggestions.

- **AI Chat (Available via the [Chrome Extension](https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/qodo-merge-ai-powered-cod/ephlnjeghhogofkifjloamocljapahnl) only):**
  Ask targeted questions about specific code changes and receive context-aware answers within the pull request comment section.

**Qodo Merge Benefits:**

- Tailor Qodo Merge to your workflows and coding practices with custom configurations, labels, and best practices.
- Fully managed: hosting, models, regular updates, and more. Installation is as simple as signing up and adding the Qodo Merge app to your GitHub/GitLab/BitBucket repo.
- Leverage top-tier models for AI-powered code reviews with GPT-4o, Claude Sonnet 4, and Gemini 2.5.
- Secure and private: No data is stored or used to train models. Qodo Merge employs zero data retention and only uses OpenAI and Claude accounts with zero data retention.

**Installation Instructions:** 
- Make sure you can see a "Configure" button at the top of the page. If the button is not visible, ensure you are logged in to GitHub account and refresh the page. 
- Click the "Configure" button and follow the instructions.

issue.body:
This pull request delivers a comprehensive set of critical security fixes, validation tests, and documentation updates for the meta-analysis chatbot codebase. The changes address major vulnerabilities, improve input validation, and document both the technical and security improvements. The repository is now significantly more secure and ready for further development or deployment.

**Security Fixes and Core Improvements**

* Fixed 5 critical security vulnerabilities, including command injection, race conditions, path traversal, memory leaks, and missing input validation, with detailed implementation and configuration documentation in `SECURITY_FIXES_DOCUMENTATION.md`.
* Enhanced security integration in `utils/security_integration.py` by fixing import issues, correcting the placement and signature of `safe_subprocess_popen`, and disabling global subprocess patching for stability. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-f5fe235781dac5beb71c79c1ee75ccf391f1159e0ed0bfaeec052a3278cdff5aR7) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-f5fe235781dac5beb71c79c1ee75ccf391f1159e0ed0bfaeec052a3278cdff5aR430) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-f5fe235781dac5beb71c79c1ee75ccf391f1159e0ed0bfaeec052a3278cdff5aL479-R487)

**Testing and Validation**

* Added `test_security_fixes.py`, a comprehensive test suite to verify the effectiveness of all major security fixes, including import checks, method availability, and input validation.

**Documentation and Reporting**

* Created `SECURITY_FIXES_DOCUMENTATION.md` to detail all security vulnerabilities, fixes, testing procedures, and configuration recommendations.
* Added `TASK_COMPLETION_REPORT.md` to summarize completed security tasks, test results, implementation details, and next steps for deployment.
* Included `PR_CREATION_TRIGGER.md` as a trigger and explanation for this pull request.

  the pull request body to generate a PR summary at any time exactly where you
  want it. You can also comment `@sourcery-ai summary` on the pull request to

SonarQube Cloud (formerly SonarCloud) is a SaaS code analysis tool designed to detect coding issues in 30+ languages, frameworks, and IaC platforms. Your code is checked against an extensive set of rules that cover many attributes of code, such as maintainability, reliability, and security issues, on each merge/pull request.

For those requiring US-based hosting, [SonarQube Cloud US](https://sonarqube.us/) offers the perfect alternative. If you need data residency outside the US or within the EU, [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/) with this GitHub app is the ideal solution.

SonarQube Cloud integrates seamlessly into your GitHub workflow and provides clear guidance for resolving any code quality and security issues detected. The majority of popular languages can be analyzed automatically; no configuration is required!

With [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/github), you get:

-   Fast, precise static analysis and feedback on your code
    
-   Support for popular languages, frameworks, and IaC tools
    
-   Free analysis for open-source projects and private projects up to max 50k LoC
    
-   Automatic analysis of pull requests and branches with results reported inline
    
-   IDE Support with [SonarQube for IDE](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarlint/) integration
    
-   Quality Gate (added as a GitHub check) acting at two different levels - first, preventing you from merging pull requests that contain issues - and later, helping you to release only clean, safe code
    
-   Sign up for SonarQube free tier and begin scanning your private and public repositories
    

A [GitHub Action](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/sonarcloud-scan) is available in the marketplace to make it easy for you (for projects where automatic analysis isn't available). SonarQube Cloud also integrates smoothly with Jenkins, CircleCI, TravisCI, CirrusCI, and many other tools.

A free tier is available that allows you to explore the benefits of SonarQube Cloud using your public and private repositories. We also provide a no-commitment, [14-day trial](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/) of SonarQube Cloud Team for unlimited team members, up to 1.9M LoC, AI CodeFix recommendations, and more. No need to speak with a sales rep or request a license key - get automatic code analysis results on your private projects in minutes! Want to see more examples of SonarCloud in action? You can [explore current Open Source projects in SonarCloud](https://sonarcloud.io/explore/projects?sort=-analysis_date) that are using the [Clean as You Code](https://www.sonarsource.com/solutions/our-unique-approach/) methodology.

What are you waiting for? SonarQube Cloud helps you consistently deliver cleaner, secure software that future developers will appreciate and your users will love. Start writing Clean Code. [Now](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/)!
